<text>Best pizza and service in Santa Monica! Whether you're in the mood for a classic or something new, SaMo's pizza selection will satisfy. They even offer a hot cheetos pizza. I'm a personal fan of the Mediterranean, which has meatballs, two cheeses, and a perfect combination of fresh veggies and seasonings. They also have fresh salads and sandwiches.

The staff at SaMo are all friendly and clearly love pizza making. You can taste the high quality of ingredients, the prices are competitive, and service is quick.

They're conveniently located right across from SaMo College and just a half-hour walk/5-10 minute drive from the beach.</text>< user_id>

<Text>The crust is nice and thin, very delicate! The sauce is very good and they fire it in a hot pizza oven. We ordered several personal size 10" pies, the pepperoni was great, but the cheese pies were a little inconsistent with the meltiness. They had a great special on a 10" cheese or pepperoni for 4.99 and 5.99 respectively, so we ordered a bunch of those. I also had a house salad that was pretty standard, but good. The pizza menu is pretty extensive, but also pretty expensive! Some of the personal size pies were like $20. I'd like to try the vegetarian pie, but don't wanna shell out $17 for a thin 10" pie from a strip mall pizza stand with 4 tables. Either step up the ambiance or drop the prices.<//Text><pics>None</pics>< response>

< Text>
Back again at the place my grandson says have the best pizzas in the WORLD. Ah, to be young again ...

The pizzas ARE quite good and their method of ordering is quite easy. You can order a pizza straight off of their menu or customize it pretty much any way you can imagine. Think of it like Subway - except the pizzas are terrific and delivered to your table piping hot.

There is a great vibe to this place and it is catchy. My grandson loves the condiment area (but likes the garlic way too much). they have a huge tree in the building along with some very neat pizza ovens. Make sure you try the Nutella Calzone.

Definitely will be back again when visiting the grandchildren. We could use something like this in New Jersey!< /Text>

<review>Pluses-
Great management.
Any repairs are always done within 24 hours.
Very quiet, dog friendly community.

Minuses-
No A/C so my 3rd floor apartment gets hot in the summer.  You will need a portable unit for your bedroom at least.
Water and sewer waste charges added to rent at approximately $65-70 per month.  Total additional charges (not including PG&E) approximately $100-$120/month so be sure to budget for that.

<Time>1479152097323</Time><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
I've lived in multiple apartment complexes in San Rafael and SF.  The people that work at Eaves are by far the most friendly, most client focused, bend over backwards for you group I have ever encountered.  From James and his office team... to the maintenance team... They truly work like a family to serve the community they oversee at Eaves.  Anna is always looking out for the residents, in the moving in/moving out process, to anything they can do to help make your living experience the best it can be at Eaves.  The community itself tends to be very quiet and peaceful... You can have bad neighbors in any community, but I haven't experienced it here..  Martin and the maintenance staff do an outstanding job, from keeping the pool safe and clean, to showing up promptly for appointments when something is in need of fixing in the apartment.  You're always welcome to come into the office, get your 4-legged animal a treat (they love your animals!) , and see what's going on in the community that week.  I will truly miss the people at Eaves as my wife and I are moving into our first home.. but, this is the best Apartment complex I've lived in during my past 4 years (and 4 apartments) in the North Bay. < text>
I came in yesterday and picked out 4 new Goodyear tires for my SUV, and arranged for them to be held for my appointment today. I come in today at 11, and they tell me the tire guy is running a little late to work. The manager proceeds to tell me there will be a wait, which I can understand. 2 hours later, the tire tech is still not in, and there is a line waiting just to be seen going out of automotive. I got my keys and left, because they had 3 lube techs and no tire guy...and nobody seems to know how to mount a tire but the guy who didn't show up.

Manager blamed it on Wal-Mart. I made sure to tell him that if he was a half decent manager, he wouldn't have left me unaware and wasting my time. He should have managed that, being he is supposed to be a manager.

Last time I was here, they messed up my power windows on another car. Guess I went against my better judgement by giving them another chance.

Go somewhere else, or take your chances at a bad experience.<//text>

1554581310588< /Time>
< rating>
2</rating>
< text>
Good prices and large selection of items for the home. However, always, always check the seals and caps of anything you buy from Walmart.  For example, cheap and unscrupulous people will buy the windshield fluid gallon for about $1.50 and use some of it, refill it with water, and return it! How do I know this? The jugs come with glued aluminum cap seals. The jugs that have been tampered will have missing seals or halfway opened seal. Also, the jugs that have been diluted with water are several shades lighter blue than the full strength jugs.  Of the dozen or so jugs that were stocked, nearly half were tampered.  Employees should check the seals of fluids before accepting returns.  I've also had issues with aftershave balm bottles that are half full or empty!  Always be skeptical and check the seals and content of everything you buy from Walmart.</text>

< Review>
I went to this place earlier today and was very impressed by not only the cost of j their units, but also by the lovely Assistant Manager, Britney, that was there. I did a lot of price checking before hand and found that this place would be well within my budget for the size I was looking for.

I have a few stuff that I've got to hold for awhile and I figured  5x10 would do the job. After explaining everything I had she strongly recommended that I get a unit one size up. My wife and I were interested in adding an additional water bib in our backyard so that we could hook up a hose.  This job involved rerouting our drip irrigation system and attaching a water bib to the side of the house.

We had a great experience with HOMEX!  Juan answered the phone and helped setup our estimate appointment for the next day.  Shortly after I setup our appointment, I received a confirmation email and a text confirmation the day of our appointment.  The text confirmation provided the name and picture of the person that was going to come out to the house.  I appreciated knowing who was going to be coming out.

When he arrived, Juan came in a truck that clearly stated the name of the company and he was dressed in the company uniform.  Juan took a look at our current situation, listened to what we wanted done and  clearly explained three different options.  One being the most cost effective, a second being a little more expensive, and a third that would have been really high end.  He explained that given everything that I told him, he would recommend going with the most cost effective option.  Throughout the whole process, I didn't feel pressured or rushed to make a decision.  I asked for a little time because I wanted to talk to my wife about the options and the job.  Again, I didn't receive any pressure.

I called back later that evening and scheduled an appointment to have the job completed.  Juan came back out and went over the options again to make sure that the job was going to meet our expectations.  Again, I didn't feel pressured and he never tried to encourage me to add on things that I didn't need such as replacing our existing pvc pipe or drip irrigation system.

Juan was extremely fast and he explained the steps before he started.  When he was finished, he showed us the completed job and gave us recommendations on maintaining the area.  Juan was professional and he did an excellent job of cleaning up the area.  I would definitely recommend HOMEX.</review>

< rating>
5< /rating>
< text>
One of my favorite Karaoke Bars in West LA, for sure. Unfortunately, do to Covid-19 there won't be Karaoke for a while. However, they do have outdoor seating available right now. I still enjoying going there because their entire staff is so friendly, prices are right, and the their food is so good! I have been going there for over 5 years and I honestly have nothing to complain about. If you're going to check out BW 11 (the local nickname) for the first time, keep in mind that you may need some patience to find parking if you're not going to take a Lyft or Uber. They are in a little corner plaza so the parking can be very limited from time to time. Lately because of the pandemic, it's been very easy to find parking.

Side note: When they do open back up to full capacity, you'll want to get there early to put you name on the list to sing, that place gets packed! Lol<//text>

<time>1580186477559</time><user_name>Ziggy Kruse< /user_name><Review>Boardwalk 11:

My husband and I were looking for a venue that offers fun, food and a good space to entertain our friends and family for an evening to celebrate his retirement and my birthday.

As usual, we went online, did a search for those types of TAGS and came across Boardwalk 11.

We looked at most of the 500+ reviews already posted, including the negative ones. Some of those are really serious: Cold old food, roaches, bad service, etc.

Most people may have been persuaded to not even consider this place, but we thought: Can it really be THAT BAD?

The answer is NO! ‚Äì We went the same day we did our research, parked in the parking lot (which is free valet [translation: If you eat or drink, incl. non-alcoholic drinks you only need to consider tipping the valet]), went inside and we started to look around.

The place was almost empty, but it was just a little after 6:30 PM on a Tuesday. There was a clear friendliness between patrons, bartender, server and newcomers like us.

We sat down near the bar, got a menu and were surprised about the prices as those are pretty competitive to other places.

Even though we felt ‚Äúadventurous‚Äù, both of us ended up with the same dish: BBQ Chicken Tostada Salad. The shell was crispy, the salad fresh and the chicken tender. ‚Äì It was good.

Still, having some of those negative reviews in mind, I kept looking for anything that would gross me out. I didn‚Äôt see anything. No Roaches, no bugs of any kind. In fact, the entire place was clean, inviting, and fun.

Our server also managed to bring the owner over to us. Which was nice, as I kept thinking about the negative review he got and I expected to meet a grumpy, old, unkempt, mean, horrid person. He is not.

Steve introduced himself and started chatting with us about the venue. He is open minded, courteous, and funny.

Even though things may change in the future, but for right now, and based on our first impression, we are looking forward to our little celebration at Boardwalk 11.</Review>< pictures>
None< /pictures>

I've walked past this place like a million times but never went in until just recently.  Imagine my surprise when I saw how clean, intimate and classy the establishment was.  It's a perfect place to bring a date or a small group of friends for local craft beer, good food and watching people sing their favorite karaoke songs.  I would definitely recommend this restaurant-bar to others and would come back again.  I knocked off a star due to it's utter lack of parking.  However, for those who happen to live in the area, it is the quintessential neighborhood bar experience and would encourage others in the Palms area to check it out.  A perfect venue for a date.</text>

<review>Awesome food and great selection and the crowd makes you feel at home<//review></record></dataset><record>
< gmapID>
0x80c2bbcb99c2200f:0xd87a5214846753a3<//gmapID>
<time>1552969041667< /time><user_id>116236137928562119114</user_id><Pics>None<//Pics><Name>Sean Dennison<//Name>< review>
I went here to enjoy a karaoke night with a new friend and got a table near the karaoke host and close to the stage. The place itself was nice enough. Lots of comfortable seating. Good sound system. Nice branded stage with good lighting. They had a charging station but I ended up grabbing an outlet closer to my table to charge my phone.

It was St. Patrick's Day so my friend and I both ordered green beers which were featured on the menu. Basically they were green versions of Miller Light which worked for us.

We both put songs in with the karaoke host immediately upon arrival and settled in at our table to look through the karaoke book with our green beers. It was posted that we could only put one song in at a time so that's what we did. I was told the wait to sing was about an hour and a half. Not being terribly long we patiently waited our turns while being entertained by the other performers.

Two and a half hours and four beers later my friend and I had still not been invited up to sing yet and I would soon have to head home to get some sleep for work the next day so I asked the karaoke host again if he could work us into the lineup soon. He said we were 7 songs away.  That would be another half an hour! 3 hours wait to sing one song??!! Which would have been twice his original estimate of one and a half hours. That was ridiculous and not ok.

Now mind you I watched certain performers get up there 2 or three times throughout the night while we waited to sing once. I am certain that the karaoke hosts math was not off when he gave the earlier time estimate but seemed to not value our time or have any integrity whatsoever and just put others before us time after time after time to add another 1.5 hours of singers between our first songs.

In the end I paid the bill and left after waiting 2.5 hours. Very dissatisfied.< /review>

< review>
I'm so sad.. I love to support local small dive bars, and this spot is super awesome. But tonight,.First of all, the prices are a little steep for what kind of bar this is.  It's a dumpy bar in a strip mall in the middle of Palms - everything should be cheap, but it's not.  I haven't been there lately, but they used to have a two drink minimum on weekend nights.  If you're not careful with what you order, those two things can add up to a pretty serious tab.

Second, I personally think the crowd here is pretty annoying.  I know people love that there are "regulars" here, but I kind of get tired of seeing the same people sing the same stuff every time I'm there.  The big groups that come here e.g. offices parties or bachelorette parties (the worst) can get quite annoying.  Although, this is probably not something unique to Boardwalk 11.

But, the main problem with this place is that on the weekend, the wait can easily be two hours (I've seen longer).  It's kind of tough to sit through people butchering songs for 2+ hours just so you can finally get your one song in.  Also, as I think maybe someone alluded to, the big groups that are there seemingly never have a problem getting their songs in.  Based on what I've seen, I think it's pretty safe to say that there's some shenanigans going on with the waiting list</review>

< Review>
I will be back!! üòÉ Thank you for making my birthday awesome!!

This place saved the day when I had to swiwtch my venue last minute. They allow birthday cakes to be brought in & they'll sing Happy Bday & have the whole bar join in! The staff here is incredible! They made it a fun special night with great drinks, food & stage! The song selection & sound equipment are excellent too!

But be warned! This place has got talent!!! I've never seen so many talented singers in a karaoke bar (but it is LA, so...)! It wasn't extremely busy (on a Thursday) so my group was able to sing 4-5 times throughout the night & the crowd had an amazing supportive energy so even if you're like me & totally suck at Karaoke lol they make you feel amazing! üòÉ

I can't wait to go again!<//Review>
